<h5>Benefits of <span style="color: red;">Red</span> and <span style="color: blue;">Blue</span> LED Light Therapy</h5>

<p>LED light therapy is non-invasive, causes no inflammation, and requires no special post treatment procedures. It is proven to be effective for cosmetic purposes, diminishing the visibility of fine lines, wrinkles, and acne.</p>

<p><img src="/images/lumaprobe.jpg" class="float-right ml-3" alt="LumaProbe" />LED light therapy:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Promotes natural production of collagen and elastin</li>
  <li>Reduces appearance of aging and damaged skin.</li>
  <li>Has no reported side effects.</li>
</ul>

<p>Precautions:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Individuals taking steroid or cortisone injections, who are pregnant, or who have a thyroid condition should consult a physician before undergoing light therapy.    </li>
  <li>LED light therapy is not recommended for individuals who are epileptic, photo-allergic, or taking medications that cause light sensitivity, such as Tetracycline.</li>
  </ul>

<h5 class="mt-3"><span style="color: red;">Red</span> Light</h5>

<p>Red light therapy is generally indicated for the treatment of fine lines, peri-orbital, and skin wrinkles.</p>

<p>A 30-minute maintenance treatment is all that is needed following the initial series of treatments.</p>

