<h5 class="mt-3"><span style="color: blue;">Blue</span> Light</h5>

<p>Acne causing bacteria known as Propionibacterium acnes (P. acne) excretes porphyrins. When these porphyrins are exposed to a specific wavelength of light (blue light from 405 to 420nm), oxygen is seperated from the porphyrin molecule, producing free radicals which kills the bacteria.</p>

<p>Treatments can be used on any part of the body and is especially effective in reducing and calming inflamed acne.</p>

